,"finishTime":10.8,"dialogue":{"text":"No worries. That's what code reviews are for.","align":"left"}},{"background":null,"character":"Sarah","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":11.3,"finishTime":14,"dialogue":{"text":"First, I'd suggest that you format the code consistently.","align":"left"}},{"background":null,"character":"Sarah","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":14.14,"finishTime":16.04,"dialogue":{"text":"It'll be easier for everyone to read.","align":"left"}},{"background":null,"character":"Tom","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":16.4,"finishTime":20.56,"dialogue":{"text":"Got it. So if I indent the blocks consistently, it improves code readability?","align":"right"}},{"background":null,"character":"Sarah","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":21.22,"finishTime":24.62,"dialogue":{"text":"Exactly. Consistent indentation makes the code visually organized.","align":"left"}},{"background":null,"character":"Sarah","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":24.86,"finishTime":27.78,"dialogue":{"text":"It's a good practice. It also helps maintainability.","align":"left"}},{"background":null,"character":"Sarah","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":28.42,"finishTime":32.3,"dialogue":{"text":"Now, let's talk about error handling. If you encounter potential issues,","align":"left"}},{"background":null,"character":"Sarah","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":32.64,"finishTime":35.98,"dialogue":{"text":"it's a good idea to use conditional statements to handle them gracefully.","align":"left"}},{"background":null,"character":"Tom","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":36.72,"finishTime":39.18,"dialogue":{"text":"So I should include conditional statements to manage them?","align":"right"}},{"background":null,"character":"Sarah","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":39.88,"finishTime":44.22,"dialogue":{"text":"Absolutely. It prevents unexpected crashes and provides a better user experience.","align":"left"}},{"background":null,"character":"Sarah","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":44.74,"finishTime":46.78,"dialogue":{"text":"To finish, let's consider the comments.","align":"left"}},{"background":null,"character":"Sarah","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":47.3,"finishTime":51.5,"dialogue":{"text":"If you include comments when they're necessary, it helps future developers understand the logic.","align":"left"}},{"background":null,"character":"Tom","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":51.68,"finishTime":55.1,"dialogue":{"text":"I see. So by explaining the complex parts with comments,","align":"right"}},{"background":null,"character":"Tom","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":55.34,"finishTime":58.26,"dialogue":{"text":"I'll help other people understand the code better. Is that right?","align":"right"}},{"background":null,"character":"Sarah","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":59,"finishTime":61.86,"dialogue":{"text":"Precisely. It's a form of documentation within the code.","align":"left"}},{"background":null,"character":"Sarah","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":62.36,"finishTime":63.92,"dialogue":{"text":"Great job grasping these concepts.","align":"left"}},{"background":null,"character":"Tom","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":64.42,"finishTime":66.44,"dialogue":{"text":"Thanks. And great tips, by the way.","align":"right"}},{"background":null,"character":"Tom","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":66.8,"finishTime":69.72,"dialogue":{"text":"I'll make those suggested changes and submit the code again.","align":"right"}},{"background":null,"character":"Tom","position":{"x":125,"y":0,"z":1},"opacity":null,"startTime":70.22,"finishTime":null,"dialogue":null},{"background":null,"character":"Sarah","position":{"x":-25,"y":0,"z":1},"opacity":null,"startTime":70.72,"finishTime":null,"dialogue":null}]},"superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","tests":[],"title":"Dialog 1: Sesija pregleda koda","transcript":null,"translationPending":false,"v